// Internal services (Admin, Config, ProxyControl, SipTrace, Edge,
// Pipeline, Registry, Scheduler) remain registered on their existing
// pods but are implementation details that may evolve / re-shard /
// rename without notice. Public consumers MUST go through OperatorAPI.
//
// Hosting: registered on media-server's existing admin gRPC listener
// (chart default :50070). One pod, one Service, one Ingress in front
// (Traefik + cert-manager + oauth2-proxy in production).
//
// Auth: same Bearer SIPMESH_API_KEY interceptor used everywhere else.
//
// Atomic deploy: ApplyOperatorConfig is the bulk-write entry point.
// Frontend builds a complete OperatorConfig (trunks + routes +
// pipelines), pushes it as one transaction. Server validates the
// whole graph — every route's `trunk` cross-references must resolve;
// every flow named in a route's `pipeline` must exist; codec lists
// validated against the binary's compiled-in registry; etc — BEFORE
